   Here is the 54-45 roll call by which the
Senate voted to approve a deficit-reduction bill containing tax
increases and spending cuts for the next five years.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to pass the bill and a
``no'' vote was a vote to defeat it.
   Voting ``yes'' were 35 Democrats and 19 Republicans.
   Voting ''no'' were 20 Democrats and 25 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
